  "slug": "the-ten-minute-reclaim-touched-out",
  "title": "The Ten-Minute Reclaim: Touched Out",
  "subtitle": "A short ritual for reclaiming your body after a day of constant physical demand",
  "excerpt": "A ten-minute ritual for the end of a day in which your body has been in constant demand from others. A bounded practice for returning your body to you before the evening ends.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education. The five-part ritual structure draws on the ceremony shape from MONEY Journal (Rebecca Page, 2025). The concept of being 'touched out' is widely discussed in maternal health writing.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A ten-minute evening ritual for the end of a day when your body has been in constant demand. The practice creates a physical boundary between the day's demands and the evening, and returns your body to you in a small, deliberate way.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to rituals? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "how rituals work",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/how-rituals-work"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Find ten minutes alone, even if that means waiting until they are in bed. Go somewhere with a door. A bathroom is fine. The point is one room with no one in it except you. Close the door. Stand or sit. Place both hands flat on your own body somewhere: your thighs, your stomach, your chest. Hold them there for thirty seconds.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Release (repeat x3)",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "pullQuote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "I am ready to release the claim this day has had on my body. I release it now. I release it now. I release it now.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Allow (repeat x3)",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "pullQuote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "I am ready to allow my body to belong to me again. I allow it now. I allow it now. I allow it now.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Integrate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spend five minutes doing one thing that is only for your body: a stretch on the floor, a hot shower, a cup of tea held with both hands, lying flat on the bed. No screen. Nothing required of you. Five minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Anchor",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "pullQuote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "text": "This body is mine. The day is done.",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Say it once. Go on with the evening.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
